hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgTable.name: hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgTable
hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgTable.description: The voice digital interface common configuration table contains information about configuration parameters for digital voice interface.

hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgEntry.name: hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgEntry
hwVoDigitalIfCommonCfgEntry.description: An entry in the voice digital interface common configuration table. The entry is automatically created when a digital voice interface hardware is found.

hwVoDigitalIfCfgPortNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfCfgPortNumber
hwVoDigitalIfCfgPortNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface common config table. It identify the number of the voice port.

hwVoDigitalIfCfgGroupNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfCfgGroupNumber
hwVoDigitalIfCfgGroupNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface common config table. It identify the number of the ds0 or pri group.

hwVoDigitalIfCfgBoardType.name: hwVoDigitalIfCfgBoardType
hwVoDigitalIfCfgBoardType.description: This object expresses the type of digital voice interface.

hwVoDigitalIfCfgSignalType.name: hwVoDigitalIfCfgSignalType
hwVoDigitalIfCfgSignalType.description: This object expresses the signal type of ds0 or pri group.

hwVoDigitalIfCfgTimeSlotsConfigurable.name: hwVoDigitalIfCfgTimeSlotsConfigurable
hwVoDigitalIfCfgTimeSlotsConfigurable.description: This object expresses whether the timeslot is available. '1' states the timeslot is available for the E1VI or T1VI, '0' states the timeslot is not available. For T1VI, the length is 24. For E1VI, the length is 32.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTable.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTable
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTable.description: The voice digital interface e&m configuration table contains information about configuration parameters for digital e&m voice interface.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgEntry.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgEntry
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgEntry.description: An entry in the voice digital interface e&m configuration table. The entry is automatically created when a digital voice interface is configed for digital e&m signal.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgPortNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgPortNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgPortNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m config table. It identify the number of the voice port.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgGroupNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgGroupNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgGroupNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m config table. It identify the number of the ds0 group.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutInterDigits.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutInterDigits
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutInterDigits.description: This object states the longest time to wait between two input digit from caller side. The default value is 10 seconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutRinging.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutRinging
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutRinging.description: This object expresses the ring timeout of the digital e&m interface. The value of 65535 indicates the timer is approach infinity. The default value of this object is 60 seconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutWaitDigit.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutWaitDigit
hwVoDigitalIfEMCfgTimeoutWaitDigit.description: This object expresses the wait digit timeout of the digital e&m interface. The value of 65535 indicates the timer is approach infinity. The default value of this object is 5 seconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgTable.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgTable
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgTable.description: The voice digital interface e&m abcd configuration table contains information about abcd bits configuration parameters for digital e&m voice interface.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgEntry.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgEntry
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgEntry.description: An entry in the voice digital interface e&m abcd configuration table. The entry is automatically created when a digital voice interface is configed for digital e&m signal.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgPortNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgPortNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgPortNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m abcd config table. It identify the number of the voice port.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgGroupNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgGroupNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDCfgGroupNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m abcd config table. It identify the number of the ds0 group.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxIdle.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxIdle
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxIdle.description: This object expresses the a b c d bits for receiving idle signal. The default value is '1101'.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxSeize.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxSeize
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDRxSeize.description: This object expresses the a b c d bits for receiving seize signal. The default value is '0101'.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxIdle.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxIdle
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxIdle.description: This object expresses the a b c d bits for sending idle signal. The default value is '1101'.

hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxSeize.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxSeize
hwVoDigitalIfEMABCDTxSeize.description: This object expresses the a b c d bits for sending seize signal. The default value is '0101'.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerTable.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerTable
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerTable.description: The voice digital interface e&m timer table contains information about timer parameters for digital e&m voice interface.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerEntry.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerEntry
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerEntry.description: An entry in the voice digital interface e&m timer table. The entry is automatically created when a digital voice interface is configed for digital e&m signal.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerPortNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerPortNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerPortNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m timer config table. It identify the number of the voice port.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerGroupNumber.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerGroupNumber
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerGroupNumber.description: Index of voice digital interface e&m timer config table. It identify the number of the ds0 group.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerCallInterval.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerCallInterval
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerCallInterval.description: This object expresses the dureation of call clearing. The default value is 200 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerSendWink.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerSendWink
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerSendWink.description: This object expresses the max time between receiving seizure signal and sending wink signal. The default value is 500 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkRising.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkRising
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkRising.description: This object expresses the max time between sending seizure signal and receiving wink signal. The default value is 1000 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkHold.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkHold
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerWinkHold.description: This object expresses the max duration for sending wink signal. The default value is 500 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDialoutDelay.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDialoutDelay
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDialoutDelay.description: This object expresses max time sending called digits. The default value is 300 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerRising.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerRising
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerRising.description: This object expresses the wait duration between receiveing seizure signal and sending delay signal. The default value is 300 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerHold.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerHold
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerHold.description: This object expresses the max time sending delay signal. The default value is 400 milliseconds.

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmf.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmf
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmf.description: This object expresses outgoing dtmf digit duration of the digital e&m interface. The default value is 120 milliseconds

hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmfInterval.name: hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmfInterval
hwVoDigitalIfEMTimerDtmfInterval.description: This object expresses outgoing dtmf inter-digit duration of the digital e&m interface. The default value is 120 milliseconds

hwVoDigitalIfR2DebounceTime.name: hwVoDigitalIfR2DebounceTime

hwVoDigitalIfR2TimeoutSendAnswer.name: hwVoDigitalIfR2TimeoutSendAnswer
